1
00:00:12,940 --> 00:00:15,810
CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
WARNER BROS.

2
00:00:22,790 --> 00:00:26,150
DEAR LORD,
WE NEED A MIRACLE.

3
00:00:26,220 --> 00:00:29,220
MAMA USED TO SAY THERE'S
2 THINGS WORTH BELIEVIN' IN--

4
00:00:29,290 --> 00:00:31,590
GOD AND ATHENS FOOTBALL.

5
00:00:33,130 --> 00:00:34,900
WELL, EVER SINCE
THE JACK SCHULER GAME,

6
00:00:34,960 --> 00:00:36,060
PEOPLE AROUND HERE

7
00:00:36,130 --> 00:00:38,570
HAVE HAD A HARD TIME
BELIEVIN' IN ANYTHING.

8
00:00:38,630 --> 00:00:41,070
THIS TOWN'S GOT
ONE FOOT IN THE GRAVE.

9
00:00:41,140 --> 00:00:43,070
IF YOU DON'T DO
SOMETHIN' SOON,

10
00:00:43,140 --> 00:00:45,070
WE'RE GONNA LOSE
MORE THAN OUR SCHOOL.

11
00:00:45,140 --> 00:00:46,170
Man: RACHEL!

12
00:00:47,810 --> 00:00:49,340
WE GOTTA GO,
SWEETHEART.

13
00:00:50,810 --> 00:00:52,410
SO, GOD...

14
00:00:52,480 --> 00:00:53,910
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

15
00:00:53,980 --> 00:00:56,920
IT'S ABOUT TIME
YOU SHOW UP AND...

16
00:00:56,990 --> 00:00:58,020
SHOW OFF.

17
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:00,350
AMEN.

18
00:01:02,160 --> 00:01:03,760
EVERY TIME
I TELL THIS STORY,

19
00:01:03,830 --> 00:01:05,590
I START
WITH THAT SIMPLE PRAYER.

20
00:01:05,660 --> 00:01:08,600
BUT THE STORY REALLY STARTS
12 YEARS BEFORE THAT DAY,

21
00:01:08,660 --> 00:01:09,930
WITH ME AND MY DAD

22
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:12,270
AT THE HIGH SCHOOL
STATE CHAMPIONSHIP.

23
00:01:12,330 --> 00:01:14,200
[BAND DRUMS BEATING RHYTHM]

24
00:01:15,810 --> 00:01:17,170
ALL RIGHT, DOGS,

25
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:19,510
THEY'RE GONNA
EXPECT US TO PASS,

26
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:22,240
BUT WE ARE GONNA
LET THE BONE ROLL.

27
00:01:22,310 --> 00:01:23,340
ALL RIGHT?

28
00:01:23,410 --> 00:01:24,380
ALL RIGHT?!

29
00:01:24,450 --> 00:01:25,380
1, 2, 3!

30
00:01:25,450 --> 00:01:26,560
BREAK!
BREAK!

31
00:01:26,630 --> 00:01:28,780
[CHEERING AND SHOUTING]

32
00:01:35,930 --> 00:01:38,690
LISTEN, SON, I DON'T WANT
ANY FOOL HEROICS OUT THERE.

33
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:40,360
THIS TEAM NEEDS YOU NOW.

34
00:01:40,430 --> 00:01:42,480
NOW, YOU'RE GONNA GO OUT THERE
AND BLOCK LIKE A BUICK.

35
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:43,630
ALL RIGHT?!

36
00:01:45,370 --> 00:01:47,270
Announcer:
ROCK HILL, 28,

37
00:01:47,340 --> 00:01:48,970
OUR CRUSADERS, 24.

38
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:50,700
WITH ONLY 8 SECONDS LEFT,

39
00:01:50,770 --> 00:01:54,680
ATHENS IS 35 YARDS AWAY FROM
THEIR 17th STATE CHAMPIONSHIP.

40
00:01:54,740 --> 00:01:56,540
COACH SCHULER
MIGHT HAVE TO RETHINK

41
00:01:56,610 --> 00:01:57,990
HIS HATRED
FOR THE PASSING GAME.

42
00:01:58,060 --> 00:01:58,980
BREAK!
BREAK!

43
00:02:12,930 --> 00:02:13,890
DOWN!

44
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,260
SET! HUT!

45
00:02:19,750 --> 00:02:20,970
[CROWD SHOUTING]

46
00:02:48,860 --> 00:02:49,800
UHH!

47
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:57,170
[GAME-END HORN BLOWS]

48
00:02:59,510 --> 00:03:00,740
Announcer:
THE GAME IS OVER.

49
00:03:00,810 --> 00:03:03,280
ROCK HILL
HAS DEFEATED ATHENS,

50
00:03:03,330 --> 00:03:05,610
BUT ALL EYES
ARE ON JACK SCHULER,

51
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:07,710
MOTIONLESS
ON THE ONE-YARD LINE.

52
00:03:07,780 --> 00:03:08,900
Coach: JACK!

53
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,050
SON?

54
00:03:19,330 --> 00:03:20,190
COME ON.

55
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:22,730
JACK.

56
00:03:24,180 --> 00:03:27,970
Announcer: COACH SCHULER
IS KNEELING OVER HIS SON.

57
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:30,900
JACK HAS NOT MOVED
SINCE HE WENT DOWN.

58
00:03:34,690 --> 00:03:37,810
COACH IS FRANTICALLY
MOTIONING FOR PARAMEDICS.

59
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,650
THIS DOES NOT LOOK GOOD.

60
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:41,280
WE'LL KEEP IT HERE
UNTIL WE KNOW MORE.

61
00:03:44,550 --> 00:03:46,520
WHY DIDN'T YOU DO
WHAT I SAID?

62
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:49,690
WHY DIDN'T YOU DO
WHAT I TOLD YOU TO DO?!

63
00:03:50,890 --> 00:03:52,590
[SOBBING] JACK.

64
00:04:33,370 --> 00:04:36,200
Rachel: WHEN COACH RETIRED
THE NEXT DAY AND LEFT TOWN,

65
00:04:36,270 --> 00:04:39,870
PEOPLE BELIEVED ATHENS TRADITION
PRETTY MUCH LEFT WITH HIM.

66
00:04:39,940 --> 00:04:42,040
HAVEN'T HAD
A WINNING SEASON SINCE.

67
00:04:42,110 --> 00:04:43,540
SO WHEN THE RUMOR STARTED

68
00:04:43,610 --> 00:04:45,710
THE COUNTY MIGHT
BE CLOSIN' THE HIGH SCHOOL,

69
00:04:45,780 --> 00:04:47,710
NO ONE REALLY CARED,

70
00:04:47,780 --> 00:04:50,320
THAT IS, UNTIL WE HEARD
THAT COACH WAS COMIN' BACK

71
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:52,390
FOR OUR LAST YEAR.

72
00:04:52,450 --> 00:04:54,990
GUESS HE COULDN'T STAND SEEIN'
WHAT HE'D BUILT END THAT WAY.

73
00:04:56,460 --> 00:04:59,590
ANYWAY, I MADE A DEAL WITH GOD
THAT IF HE'D DO HIS PART

74
00:04:59,660 --> 00:05:02,430
TO KEEP THIS TOWN ALIVE,
I'D DO MINE.

75
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:05,270
RACHEL!

76
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:08,800
GOTTA GO, SWEETHEART.

77
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:17,080
SO, GOD,
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

78
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:22,180
IT'S ABOUT TIME YOU
SHOW UP AND SHOW OFF.

79
00:05:22,250 --> 00:05:23,220
AMEN.

80
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:40,700
♪ WELL, I BEEN DREAMIN'
SINCE YESTERDAY EVENIN' ♪

81
00:05:40,770 --> 00:05:44,970
♪ ABOUT A TIME AND A PLACE
WHERE I CAN BREATHE... ♪

82
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,270
Reporter:
ATHENS, ALABAMA,

83
00:05:46,340 --> 00:05:48,510
ONCE THE FOOTBALL CAPITAL
OF THE SOUTH.

84
00:05:48,580 --> 00:05:52,380
16 STATE CHAMPIONSHIPS
SINCE 1923.

85
00:05:52,450 --> 00:05:54,980
BEAR BRYANT ONCE CALLED
ATHENS "THE MOTHER LODE

86
00:05:55,050 --> 00:05:56,580
OF ALL-AMERICAN
FOOTBALL PLAYERS."

87
00:05:57,950 --> 00:06:01,690
♪ NEAR THE EDGE
OF THE CROWD ♪

88
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:03,790
♪ I HEAR THE ANGELS ♪

89
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:09,960
♪ CALLING MY NAME
OUT LOUD ♪

90
00:06:10,030 --> 00:06:12,330
DOZENS OF STUDENTS COME OUT
EACH YEAR TO TRY OUT

91
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:15,140
FOR THE ATHENS FOOTBALL TEAM
IN HOPES OF LANDING

92
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:17,370
THE JACK F. SCHULER
SCHOLARSHIP.

93
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:18,940
THE TOWN PROVIDES
A FREE RIDE

94
00:06:19,010 --> 00:06:22,140
TO THE UNIVERSITY OF ALABAMA
FOR ONE STUDENT EACH YEAR

95
00:06:22,210 --> 00:06:23,940
TO HONOR THE MEMORY
OF THE QUARTERBACK

96
00:06:24,010 --> 00:06:25,980
WHO WAS KILLED IN
THE STATE CHAMPIONSHIP GAME

97
00:06:26,050 --> 00:06:27,080
12 YEARS AGO.

98
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:31,250
♪ YOU'LL NEVER
TAKE ME DOWN ♪

99
00:06:39,330 --> 00:06:42,230
BUT FOOTBALL IN THIS TOWN
HAS SEEN BETTER DAYS.

100
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:43,460
THEY HAVEN'T HAD
A WINNING SEASON

101
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:45,200
SINCE THAT INFAMOUS GAME,

102
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:47,600
AND COUNTY CUTBACKS
HAVE DOOMED THIS SCHOOL

103
00:06:47,670 --> 00:06:49,700
FOR CLOSURE
AT THE END OF THE YEAR.

104
00:06:49,770 --> 00:06:52,270
♪ IS GOIN' DOWN ♪

105
00:06:52,340 --> 00:06:54,780
♪ NO NEED
TO HAND ME LIES ♪

106
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:57,080
♪ NO NEED
TO SCRUTINIZE ♪

107
00:06:57,150 --> 00:06:59,710
♪ 'CAUSE I KNOW THE WAY
THE WORLD WORKS ♪

108
00:06:59,780 --> 00:07:02,620
♪ AND THE WAY THE EARTH
SPINS ROUND... ♪

109
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:04,450
BUT IF THERE WAS EVER
A GLIMMER OF HOPE

110
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:05,690
FOR THIS TOWN,

111
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:08,690
IT COMES IN THE NAME
OF COACH BUSTER SCHULER.

112
00:07:08,760 --> 00:07:09,690
THE LEGENDARY COACH

113
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:11,590
WHO RETIRED
AFTER THE DEATH OF HIS SON

114
00:07:11,660 --> 00:07:14,190
IS NOW RETURNING
FOR ATHENS' LAST YEAR,

115
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:16,600
AND WHEN A LEGEND
COMES OUT OF RETIREMENT,

116
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:18,900
THE FOOTBALL WORLD
TAKES NOTICE.

117
00:07:18,970 --> 00:07:21,700
♪ YOU'LL NEVER
TAKE ME DOWN ♪

118
00:07:21,770 --> 00:07:22,970
♪ OH, NO, NO ♪

119
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:26,840
♪ YOU'LL NEVER
TAKE ME DOWN ♪

120
00:07:26,910 --> 00:07:28,980
♪ WELL, YOU CAN TIE ME UP ♪

121
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:33,480
♪ AND DRAG ME
TO THE EDGE OF THE WORLD ♪

122
00:07:33,550 --> 00:07:36,550
♪ YOU'LL NEVER
TAKE ME DOWN ♪

123
00:07:43,940 --> 00:07:48,030
YOU KNOW, I DON'T KNOW
IF WE HAVE ENOUGH.

124
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:50,000
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY ALL THESE PEOPLE COME

125
00:07:50,070 --> 00:07:51,350
JUST TO WATCH TRYOUTS.

126
00:07:51,420 --> 00:07:54,380
ONE WORD:
SCHOLARSHIP.

127
00:07:54,450 --> 00:07:57,340
2 WORDS:

128
00:07:57,410 --> 00:07:58,540
NO LIFE.

129
00:08:05,250 --> 00:08:07,510
SHOW 'EM WHAT YOU GOT, BABY.

130
00:08:07,580 --> 00:08:09,080
LET THE BONE ROLL.

131
00:08:09,130 --> 00:08:11,550
HI, MAMA!

132
00:08:11,620 --> 00:08:14,020
SHE DRESS YOU THIS MORNING,
TOO, NATERS?

133
00:08:14,090 --> 00:08:16,160
WELL, I'LL SEE YOU WHEN
WE DOIN' TACKLING DRILLS, HUH?

134
00:08:16,230 --> 00:08:17,160
NONE OF Y'ALL
GONNA BE LEFT.

135
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:19,140
I'M GONNA WIN
THAT SCHOLARSHIP, BOYS.

136
00:08:19,210 --> 00:08:21,190
WHOA, GIVE ME A LITTLE
PUFFY-PUFF ON THAT

137
00:08:21,260 --> 00:08:22,900
BEFORE YOU THROW IT OUT.

138
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:25,370
MORNING, TEE.

139
00:08:25,430 --> 00:08:26,600
MORNING.

140
00:08:26,670 --> 00:08:29,070
YOU KNOW, I WAS JUST
THINKING THAT YOUR DINER

141
00:08:29,140 --> 00:08:32,310
WOULD BE A GREAT PLACE
TO PUT THESE PAMPHLETS.

142
00:08:32,370 --> 00:08:33,840
SWEETHEART,
IT'S A DEAD END,

143
00:08:33,910 --> 00:08:34,910
AND I DON'T
WANT MY CUSTOMERS

144
00:08:34,980 --> 00:08:36,940
TO HAVE A DAILY
REMINDER OF IT.

145
00:08:37,010 --> 00:08:38,210
OH, COME ON, TEE,

146
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:39,710
YOU'VE BEEN HERE
A LONG TIME.

147
00:08:39,780 --> 00:08:42,780
THIS TOWN
HAS GIVEN YOU A LOT.

148
00:08:42,850 --> 00:08:44,450
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA
GIVE BACK?

149
00:08:52,030 --> 00:08:53,890
THANK YOU.

150
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,500
[CHUCKLES]

151
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:20,720
Quarterback:
DOWN! SET! HUT!

152
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:24,020
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

153
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,140
Quarterback: LINE IT UP!

154
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,140
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

155
00:09:37,210 --> 00:09:38,700
LINE IT UP. HUT!

156
00:09:42,310 --> 00:09:45,950
VINCE LOMBARDI ONCE SAID,
"A GREAT COACH IS 50% TEACHER

157
00:09:46,010 --> 00:09:48,180
AND 50% S.O.B."

158
00:09:48,250 --> 00:09:50,980
I WANT TO THANK YOU ALL FOR
YOUR TIME AND YOUR SPIRIT.

159
00:09:51,050 --> 00:09:52,090
BUT RIGHT NOW,

160
00:09:52,150 --> 00:09:54,890
I WANT ANYBODY WHO IS
NOT WEARING A JOCKSTRAP

161
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:56,360
TO GET OFF MY FIELD.

162
00:09:56,430 --> 00:09:58,460
THANK YOU FOR COMING,
NOW, BYE-BYE.

163
00:10:00,060 --> 00:10:01,910
50%.

164
00:10:13,810 --> 00:10:14,670
Man: COACH.

165
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:18,910
ALL RIGHT, YOU DOGS
THAT ARE LEFT...

166
00:10:21,650 --> 00:10:23,780
YOU SMELL THAT?

167
00:10:23,850 --> 00:10:24,780
WHAT IS THAT?

168
00:10:24,850 --> 00:10:25,720
[SNIFFS]

169
00:10:31,580 --> 00:10:33,590
YEAH, THAT'S IT.

170
00:10:33,660 --> 00:10:35,930
THAT'S IT.
EVERYBODY ON YOUR FACES.

171
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,200
DOWN ON YOUR FACES!

172
00:10:37,250 --> 00:10:39,870
OLD MAN'S CRAZIER
THAN WE HEARD.

173
00:10:39,930 --> 00:10:41,100
NOW BREATHE DEEP.

174
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:43,940
DO YOU SMELL IT?

175
00:10:46,510 --> 00:10:48,710
THAT, DOGS,
IS THE SMELL OF DEATH.

176
00:10:50,350 --> 00:10:52,950
OVER A DECADE
OF DEAD HOPES AND DREAMS

177
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:54,580
BURIED RIGHT HERE.

178
00:10:56,780 --> 00:10:58,150
THE CURSE OF INDIVIDUALISM

179
00:10:58,220 --> 00:10:59,790
GROWS LIKE A WEED
ON THIS FIELD.

180
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:04,190
A CURSE THAT WE CALL

181
00:11:04,260 --> 00:11:07,190
THE JACK F. SCHULER
SCHOLARSHIP.

182
00:11:08,550 --> 00:11:10,260
I DIDN'T SAY
TO LIFT YOUR HEAD, SON.

183
00:11:10,330 --> 00:11:11,480
KEEP YOUR FACE
IN THE GRASS.

184
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:15,370
IT FOSTERS
VISIONS OF GRANDEUR,

185
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:17,540
DREAMS OF PERSONAL GLORY.

186
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:20,840
IT GUARANTEES DISUNITY...

187
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:24,340
AND PRIDEFUL INDIVIDUALISM,

188
00:11:24,410 --> 00:11:26,180
AND WORST OF ALL,
WORST OF ALL...

189
00:11:28,850 --> 00:11:30,720
LOSING SEASONS.

190
00:11:33,020 --> 00:11:34,520
HEAR THIS, DOGS:

191
00:11:34,590 --> 00:11:39,140
I AM THE CURE
TO THIS CURSE.

192
00:11:39,210 --> 00:11:40,690
[CHEERING AND SHOUTING]

193
00:11:45,630 --> 00:11:46,570
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

194
00:11:46,630 --> 00:11:48,200
SON, COME ON.

195
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:50,600
THANKS FOR COMIN' OUT.
BAND PRACTICE IN THE GYM.

196
00:11:59,780 --> 00:12:01,580
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

197
00:12:01,650 --> 00:12:03,480
JOHN, THANKS, BUT
UNLESS YOU CAN KICK,

198
00:12:03,550 --> 00:12:05,250
I DON'T WANT ANYBODY
UNDER 165.

199
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:07,190
ALL RIGHT, THIS IS
5-A COMPETITION.

200
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:09,120
I WANT BOYS RAISED
ON MEAT AND POTATOES.

201
00:12:09,190 --> 00:12:11,420
I LIKE MY STEAK RARE
AND POTATOES MASHED,

202
00:12:11,490 --> 00:12:12,860
AND I'M 173.

203
00:12:12,930 --> 00:12:14,090
SON...

204
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:16,360
DON'T EVER,
EVER STICK YOUR PAW

205
00:12:16,430 --> 00:12:17,860
IN THIS CAGE.

206
00:12:17,930 --> 00:12:19,700
YOU GONNA PAY
FOR THAT IN SWEAT.

207
00:12:21,970 --> 00:12:22,970
HUT!

208
00:12:35,870 --> 00:12:42,090
Coach Schuler: UP, DOWN.
UP, DOWN. UP, DOWN, UP.

209
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,020
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

210
00:12:48,130 --> 00:12:49,260
ALL RIGHT.

211
00:12:49,330 --> 00:12:51,130
YOU ALL RIGHT, SON?
THANKS FOR COMIN' OUT.

212
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,470
I HEAR THE SOCCER TEAM
NEEDS A LITTLE HELP.

213
00:12:52,530 --> 00:12:53,470
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

214
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:56,550
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

215
00:12:58,010 --> 00:12:59,090
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

216
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:00,570
All: ARRRRR!

217
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:04,880
DO YOU LIKE FOOTBALL!

218
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:07,180
MOVE THOSE FEET!
MOVE THOSE FEET!

219
00:13:07,250 --> 00:13:09,150
[ALL GRUNT]

220
00:13:09,220 --> 00:13:10,570
DO YOU LIKE FOOTBALL?

221
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:31,300
124.

222
00:13:31,370 --> 00:13:34,170
SORRY, SON. THANKS FOR
COMIN' OUT. STEP DOWN.

223
00:13:36,140 --> 00:13:37,240
OHH.

224
00:13:37,310 --> 00:13:38,840
YOU GOTTA BE KIDDIN' ME.

225
00:13:38,910 --> 00:13:40,810
ELVIS JACKSON.

226
00:13:47,920 --> 00:13:48,820
HMM.

227
00:13:50,490 --> 00:13:52,360
171.

228
00:13:52,430 --> 00:13:53,590
SCALE'S LIGHT.

229
00:13:53,660 --> 00:13:56,550
YOU ARE.
WITHOUT A DOUBT.

230
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,340
SHERMAN NATERS.

231
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:07,110
SHERMANATOR.

232
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:08,710
[CHUCKLES]

233
00:14:08,780 --> 00:14:09,740
ALL RIGHT.

234
00:14:17,350 --> 00:14:19,720
165.

235
00:14:19,790 --> 00:14:20,850
THAT'S RIGHT, BABY.

236
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:24,220
ONE SMALL STEP
FOR ATHENS FOOTBALL

237
00:14:24,290 --> 00:14:27,560
AND ONE GIANT STEP BACKWARDS
FOR WOMEN'S RIGHTS.

238
00:14:27,630 --> 00:14:28,490
MM-HMM.

239
00:14:30,900 --> 00:14:33,130
OHH, OH, NO. NUMBER 40.

240
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:35,000
I MEAN, MANDATORY SWAP.

241
00:14:35,070 --> 00:14:38,790
IT'S ARTICLE 3, SECTION 2
OF THE EX-BOYFRIEND MANUAL.

242
00:14:38,860 --> 00:14:42,070
SO IT'S THE EX-BOYFRIEND
MANUAL AGAIN.

243
00:14:42,140 --> 00:14:45,780
