01:10:00,430 --> 01:10:03,230
AND HIS MIRACLE SQUAD
OF 15 PLAYERS.

1230
01:10:03,290 --> 01:10:04,530
IN THEIR FINAL SEASON,

1231
01:10:04,600 --> 01:10:06,300
THE CRUSADERS
HAVE THEIR EYES SET

1232
01:10:06,360 --> 01:10:07,850
ON THE STATE CHAMPIONSHIP.

1233
01:10:07,920 --> 01:10:10,030
PEOPLE IN EVERY CORNER
OF ALABAMA

1234
01:10:10,100 --> 01:10:11,600
ARE ASKING ONE QUESTION:

1235
01:10:11,670 --> 01:10:14,370
CAN LIGHTNING
KEEP STRIKING AT THIS FIELD?

1236
01:10:14,440 --> 01:10:15,640
All: YEAH!

1237
01:10:15,710 --> 01:10:18,510
[APPLAUSE AND CHEERING]

1238
01:10:21,310 --> 01:10:25,620
♪ I WISH YOU
OUT OF THE WOODS ♪

1239
01:10:25,680 --> 01:10:29,290
♪ AND INTO A PICTURE ♪

1240
01:10:29,350 --> 01:10:31,320
♪ WITH ME ♪

1241
01:10:35,490 --> 01:10:40,000
♪ I WISH YOU
OVER THE MOON ♪

1242
01:10:40,060 --> 01:10:43,670
♪ COME OUT
OF THE QUESTION ♪

1243
01:10:43,740 --> 01:10:44,970
♪ AND BE ♪

1244
01:10:45,040 --> 01:10:47,000
THIS IS WHAT
I WANTED YOU TO SEE.

1245
01:10:49,970 --> 01:10:56,610
♪ IF THIS IS GONNA
RUN ROUND IN MY HEAD... ♪

1246
01:10:56,680 --> 01:10:59,820
AFTER MY MOM DIED,
I USED TO COME HERE.

1247
01:11:02,020 --> 01:11:04,120
I'D SPEND HOURS.

1248
01:11:05,960 --> 01:11:07,760
WHO ARE THESE PEOPLE?

1249
01:11:07,830 --> 01:11:11,530
DO YOU KNOW ANY OF THEM?

1250
01:11:11,600 --> 01:11:13,500
ONLY A FEW.

1251
01:11:13,570 --> 01:11:15,730
[CHUCKLES]

1252
01:11:15,800 --> 01:11:17,500
I WOULD MAKE UP
THESE STORIES,

1253
01:11:17,570 --> 01:11:20,540
YOU KNOW, ABOUT
WHO THEY WERE

1254
01:11:20,610 --> 01:11:23,470
AND WHY
THEY CAME HERE.

1255
01:11:26,580 --> 01:11:27,990
THIS IS INCREDIBLE.

1256
01:11:28,060 --> 01:11:31,400
LOOK AT ALL
OF THESE NAMES.

1257
01:11:33,220 --> 01:11:37,390
YOU KNOW, THIS USED
TO BE THE HEART OF ATHENS.

1258
01:11:37,460 --> 01:11:40,760
A TRAIN WOULD
COME IN HERE EVERY DAY.

1259
01:11:40,830 --> 01:11:43,160
PEOPLE COMIN'...

1260
01:11:43,230 --> 01:11:45,160
AND PEOPLE GOIN'.

1261
01:11:48,870 --> 01:11:53,340
THEN ONE DAY
THE TRAIN STOPPED COMING,

1262
01:11:53,400 --> 01:11:56,470
AND THESE 3 CARS
NEVER LEFT.

1263
01:11:58,580 --> 01:12:00,910
NOW THE TRACKS
ARE ONLY A BLOCK LONG,

1264
01:12:00,980 --> 01:12:02,750
AND IT'S
JUST LIKE EVERYBODY

1265
01:12:02,810 --> 01:12:05,260
JUST KIND
OF FORGOT ABOUT IT.

1266
01:12:05,330 --> 01:12:09,200
NOT EVERYBODY.

1267
01:12:09,270 --> 01:12:13,490
I WONDER IF THESE PEOPLE
EVEN REMEMBER COMING HERE.

1268
01:12:17,060 --> 01:12:18,790
A LOT OF MEMORIES.

1269
01:12:27,540 --> 01:12:29,670
YOU KNOW...

1270
01:12:29,740 --> 01:12:33,210
A GENTLEMAN
WOULD WALK ME HOME.

1271
01:12:33,280 --> 01:12:35,060
LET ME KNOW
WHEN YOU FIND ONE.

1272
01:12:39,150 --> 01:12:40,950
[LAUGHS]

1273
01:12:42,620 --> 01:12:45,340
Announcer: DOWN BY ONE
ON THE 45-YARD LINE,

1274
01:12:45,410 --> 01:12:47,170
YOU GOTTA THINK BRIAN
SCHULER'S THROWING DEEP.

1275
01:12:47,240 --> 01:12:48,810
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU.

1276
01:12:48,880 --> 01:12:50,880
THIS IS YOUR WHOLE
SEASON ON THE LINE.

1277
01:12:50,950 --> 01:12:53,280
WE HAVE GOT TO THROW
THE FOOTBALL, OK?

1278
01:12:53,350 --> 01:12:54,780
THAT IS EXACTLY

1279
01:12:54,850 --> 01:12:57,250
WHAT THEY ARE
EXPECTING US TO DO.

1280
01:12:57,320 --> 01:13:00,090
LISTEN, YOU GET THE BALL,
YOU GET OUT OF BOUNDS.

1281
01:13:00,150 --> 01:13:01,720
Assistant: LET'S
GO GET 'EM NOW!

1282
01:13:01,790 --> 01:13:04,760
SON, THIS TEAM NEEDS YOU.

1283
01:13:04,830 --> 01:13:05,930
NOW YOU BE A BUICK.

1284
01:13:05,990 --> 01:13:07,760
Man: LET'S GO,
BOYS, COME ON!

1285
01:13:07,830 --> 01:13:11,000
WE GOTTA PUT
THIS ONE IN THE AIR.

1286
01:13:11,080 --> 01:13:16,500
LISTEN UP.
BLUE 32. BLUE 32.

1287
01:13:16,570 --> 01:13:17,870
YOUR BUTT'S
ON THE LINE.

1288
01:13:17,940 --> 01:13:19,370
JUST WHERE
I LIKE IT.

1289
01:13:19,440 --> 01:13:20,510
ON 2. READY?

1290
01:13:20,570 --> 01:13:21,540
All: BREAK!

1291
01:13:21,610 --> 01:13:23,860
[SCHOOL BAND PLAYING]

1292
01:13:23,930 --> 01:13:27,410
32! 32! HUT!

1293
01:13:36,560 --> 01:13:38,190
ELVIS!

1294
01:13:41,030 --> 01:13:42,560
GET OUT OF BOUNDS!

1295
01:13:45,780 --> 01:13:46,880
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1296
01:13:46,950 --> 01:13:48,530
[CROWD MOANS]

1297
01:13:49,920 --> 01:13:52,470
NO, NO.

1298
01:13:53,670 --> 01:13:54,670
Announcer:
AND ATHENS IS FORCED

1299
01:13:54,740 --> 01:13:56,810
TO USE ITS FINAL TIME-OUT.

1300
01:13:56,880 --> 01:13:59,080
AND JACKSON
IS NOT GETTIN' UP.

1301
01:13:59,150 --> 01:14:01,780
HE'S HOLDIN' HIS RIGHT ARM.

1302
01:14:03,990 --> 01:14:05,400
UHH!

1303
01:14:05,470 --> 01:14:08,150
[GROANING]

1304
01:14:08,220 --> 01:14:09,150
TAKE IT EASY, SON.

1305
01:14:09,220 --> 01:14:10,690
OHH!

1306
01:14:10,760 --> 01:14:12,590
WHY DIDN'T YOU
LISTEN TO ME?

1307
01:14:12,660 --> 01:14:14,390
UHH! I'M SORRY.

1308
01:14:14,460 --> 01:14:17,560
GET HIM UP.
LET'S GO, A LITTLE HELP.

1309
01:14:17,630 --> 01:14:19,880
LET'S GO!
A LITTLE HELP HERE!

1310
01:14:19,950 --> 01:14:22,230
WATCH THE ARM.
COME ON.

1311
01:14:23,910 --> 01:14:26,540
WHAT IS
SNOOT'S BEST KICK?

1312
01:14:26,610 --> 01:14:28,210
HALF OF THIS.

1313
01:14:28,280 --> 01:14:31,390
HMM. SNOOT!

1314
01:14:31,460 --> 01:14:33,210
STRETCH YOUR HAMMY.

1315
01:14:33,280 --> 01:14:34,750
SNOOT.

1316
01:14:34,820 --> 01:14:35,810
BAIL ME OUT.

1317
01:14:35,880 --> 01:14:37,150
Announcer:
AND ATHENS' DREAMS

1318
01:14:37,220 --> 01:14:38,750
OF GETTING TO
THE STATE CHAMPIONSHIP

1319
01:14:38,820 --> 01:14:41,850
RESTS ON THE LEG
OF 5'4" SNOOT NINO

1320
01:14:41,920 --> 01:14:45,220
WHO'LL ATTEMPT A 45-YARDER,
HIS LONGEST EVER.

1321
01:14:45,290 --> 01:14:47,890
HERE'S THE SNAP, THE HOLD,
THE KICK IS UP.

1322
01:14:47,960 --> 01:14:52,060
IT'S GOOD! AND
WE'LL SEE YOU NEXT WEEK!

1323
01:14:53,800 --> 01:14:55,100
I ALWAYS THOUGHT
THE FIRST TIME

1324
01:14:55,170 --> 01:14:58,040
I'D BE HERE,

1325
01:14:58,110 --> 01:15:00,170
IT'D BE UNDER
DIFFERENT CIRCUMSTANCES.

1326
01:15:03,110 --> 01:15:05,310
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOUR DAD TRUSTS ME HERE.

1327
01:15:05,380 --> 01:15:07,250
OH, HE DOESN'T.

1328
01:15:07,320 --> 01:15:08,330
HE TRUSTS ME.

1329
01:15:10,320 --> 01:15:12,650
OK, HALFTIME IS OVER.

1330
01:15:12,720 --> 01:15:14,750
BACK TO 1782.

1331
01:15:19,960 --> 01:15:22,230
YOU'RE NOT THINKING
OF PLAYING?

1332
01:15:22,300 --> 01:15:26,170
MY SCHOLARSHIP'S
WITHIN REACH.

1333
01:15:26,230 --> 01:15:28,270
YOU MEAN
CHAMPIONSHIP?

1334
01:15:28,340 --> 01:15:29,800
RIGHT.

1335
01:15:32,940 --> 01:15:34,960
NO WONDER YOU DIDN'T
GET OUT OF BOUNDS.

1336
01:15:35,030 --> 01:15:38,310
A CHAMPIONSHIP DOES NOT
GET ME TO THE NEXT LEVEL.

1337
01:15:38,380 --> 01:15:41,350
I CAN'T WIN.

1338
01:15:41,420 --> 01:15:44,050
LOSE THE SCHOLARSHIP,
YOU'RE GONE.

1339
01:15:44,120 --> 01:15:45,620
KEEP THE SCHOLARSHIP,

1340
01:15:45,690 --> 01:15:48,000
YOU'RE GONE.

1341
01:15:48,070 --> 01:15:50,620
ELVIS, WHY SHOULD I
HAVE TO APOLOGIZE

1342
01:15:50,690 --> 01:15:54,830
FOR SOMETHING THAT PEOPLE
ARE STARTING TO BELIEVE IN?

1343
01:15:54,900 --> 01:15:57,330
PEOPLE WANNA BELIEVE
IN SOMETHING.

1344
01:15:59,670 --> 01:16:01,000
MAYBE EVEN YOU.

1345
01:16:05,240 --> 01:16:07,470
I LOVE A GOOD FIGHT.

1346
01:16:09,680 --> 01:16:12,740
ELVIS.

1347
01:16:12,810 --> 01:16:14,710
HAVE YOU EVER
DARED TO THINK

1348
01:16:14,780 --> 01:16:16,900
THERE MIGHT BE
SOMETHING BIGGER THAN YOU?

1349
01:16:20,190 --> 01:16:21,150
[CLEARS THROAT]

1350
01:16:21,220 --> 01:16:25,260
HALFTIME IS OVER.
BACK TO 1782.

1351
01:17:56,250 --> 01:17:58,950
LOOKS A LOT DIFFERENT
FROM UP HERE.

1352
01:18:01,990 --> 01:18:04,120
YOU TRYIN'
TO PLAY FRIDAY?

1353
01:18:07,060 --> 01:18:12,130
DO YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
ON DECEMBER 12, 1965?

1354
01:18:14,640 --> 01:18:16,600
THE GALE SAYERS
GAME.

1355
01:18:21,280 --> 01:18:23,580
MY DAD WAS AT THAT GAME.

1356
01:18:25,510 --> 01:18:27,680
THINK OF IT.
HE WENT TO ONE PRO GAME

1357
01:18:27,750 --> 01:18:31,280
HIS ENTIRE LIFE,
HAPPENED TO BE THAT ONE.

1358
01:18:34,660 --> 01:18:37,720
ONE OF MY ONLY MEMORIES
OF MY DAD WAS...

1359
01:18:37,790 --> 01:18:40,760
LISTENING TO HIM
DESCRIBE THAT GAME.

1360
01:18:42,800 --> 01:18:43,900
AND HE ALWAYS SAID

1361
01:18:43,960 --> 01:18:45,930
I COULD PLAY
LIKE THAT SOMEDAY.

1362
01:18:46,000 --> 01:18:51,000
I GOT ONE MORE CHANCE
TO PLAY LIKE THAT.

1363
01:18:51,070 --> 01:18:52,740
YOU KNOW, JACKSON,

1364
01:18:52,810 --> 01:18:55,910
YOU AND I ARE
A LITTLE BIT ALIKE.

1365
01:18:55,980 --> 01:18:57,510
WHEN I WAS A KID,

1366
01:18:57,580 --> 01:19:00,480
MY MOM AND DADDY
HAD TO CONSTANTLY...

1367
01:19:00,550 --> 01:19:02,350
KEEP AN EYE ON ME.

1368
01:19:04,920 --> 01:19:07,150
ONE--ONE TIME
IN THE WINTER,

1369
01:19:07,220 --> 01:19:10,490
I RUN ACROSS THE ROAD
TO A NEIGHBOR'S FROZEN POND.

1370
01:19:10,560 --> 01:19:11,820
AND THE ICE
COULDN'T HAVE BEEN MORE

1371
01:19:11,890 --> 01:19:13,120
THAN A COUPLE
OF INCHES THICK,

1372
01:19:13,190 --> 01:19:15,930
SO MY DADDY
HAD TO STAND AT THE EDGE

1373
01:19:16,000 --> 01:19:18,080
AND PLEAD WITH ME
TO GET OFF.

1374
01:19:20,670 --> 01:19:22,170
BUT SEEMED LIKE
THE MORE HE PLEADED,

1375
01:19:22,240 --> 01:19:24,870
THE MORE I WANTED
TO STAY ON THE ICE.

1376
01:19:27,140 --> 01:19:29,680
WELL, HE WAS
JUST LOOKIN' OUT

1377
01:19:29,740 --> 01:19:30,780
FOR MY BEST INTERESTS.

1378
01:19:30,840 --> 01:19:34,280
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT
AT THE TIME.

1379
01:19:34,350 --> 01:19:37,850
IT'S A LESSON MY SON
NEVER LEARNED, EITHER.

1380
01:19:37,920 --> 01:19:41,740
NOW, SON, I DON'T KNOW
WHY YOU'RE HERE.

1381
01:19:41,810 --> 01:19:43,590
WE ALL PLAY ON THIS FIELD
FOR DIFFERENT REASONS,

1382
01:19:43,660 --> 01:19:46,390
BUT I'VE NEVER SEEN
ANYBODY DO WHAT YOU DO.

1383
01:19:49,230 --> 01:19:54,130
AND IF YOU CAN LEARN
WHAT MY SON NEVER LEARNED,

1384
01:19:54,200 --> 01:19:56,740
WELL, YOU WON'T NEED
HIS SCHOLARSHIP.

1385
01:20:02,040 --> 01:20:04,740
I DIDN'T GET IT,
DID I?

1386
01:20:07,880 --> 01:20:10,720
THERE'S NOT A DIME
IN MY BOY'S FUND.

1387
01:20:10,780 --> 01:20:11,920
THE TOWN IS BROKE.

1388
01:20:14,990 --> 01:20:17,460
I JUST FOUND OUT.

1389
01:20:17,520 --> 01:20:19,090
I'M SORRY.

1390
01:20:42,780 --> 01:20:44,450
Announcer:
WHEN THE STATE CHAMPIONSHIP

1391
01:20:44,540 --> 01:20:46,220
WAS SCHEDULED
AT ATHENS STADIUM,

1392
01:20:46,290 --> 01:20:47,590
NO ONE EXPECTED
THE CRUSADERS

1393
01:20:47,660 --> 01:20:49,150
TO BE PLAYIN' IN IT.

1394
01:20:49,220 --> 01:20:51,360
BUT IT'S A BITTERSWEET DAY
IN ATHENS WITH THE NEWS

1395
01:20:51,430 --> 01:20:54,660
THAT TONIGHT'S GAME
VERSUS ROCK HILL WILL INDEED

1396
01:20:54,730 --> 01:20:56,830
BE THE LAST GAME
IN OUR HISTORY.

1397
01:20:56,900 --> 01:20:59,000
THE COUNTY REPORTS
THAT THE MONEY

1398
01:20:59,070 --> 01:21:01,130
SIMPLY ISN'T THERE,
AND STARTING NEXT YEAR

1399
01:21:01,200 --> 01:21:04,140
ATHENS STUDENTS WILL BE
TRANSFERRED TO ROCK HILL.

1400
01:21:04,200 --> 01:21:06,570
TONIGHT, THE ROCK HILL
FOOTBALL JUGGERNAUT

1401
01:21:06,640 --> 01:21:07,740
IS EXPECTED TO TOY

1402
01:21:07,810 --> 01:21:10,110
WITH THE UNDERMANNED
CRUSADERS

1403
01:21:10,180 --> 01:21:12,010
WHO HAVEN'T BEEN
TO THIS GAME IN 12 YEARS

1404
01:21:12,080 --> 01:21:13,710
AND WILL PLAY
WITHOUT INJURED STAR

1405
01:21:13,780 --> 01:21:15,550
RUNNING BACK ELVIS JACKSON.

1406
01:21:15,620 --> 01:21:18,850
BUT FOR ATHENS, TONIGHT
IS NOT A TIME TO MOURN.

1407
01:21:18,920 --> 01:21:21,450
FANS ARE EXPECTED TO COME
FROM ALL OVER ALABAMA

1408
01:21:21,520 --> 01:21:24,120
TO CELEBRATE
THE GREAT HISTORY

1409
01:21:24,190 --> 01:21:25,560
OF OUR FOOTBALL PROGRAM.

1410
01:21:30,600 --> 01:21:31,660
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'?

1411
01:21:31,730 --> 01:21:34,030
DIDN'T YOU HEAR?
WE BOTH LOST.

1412
01:21:34,100 --> 01:21:36,600
BUT I'M NOT
LEAVING TOWN.

1413
01:21:36,670 --> 01:21:38,640
I DON'T HAVE
WHAT YOU HAVE.

1414
01:21:38,710 --> 01:21:40,440
BUT YOU COULD.

1415
01:21:40,510 --> 01:21:42,440
YOU'RE HERE.

1416
01:21:42,510 --> 01:21:44,680
AND IT IS ALL RIGHT
HERE IN FRONT OF YOU,

1417
01:21:44,750 --> 01:21:45,710
AND YOU ARE PART OF IT

1418
01:21:45,780 --> 01:21:46,780
BECAUSE
YOU'VE CHANGED IT.

1419
01:21:46,850 --> 01:21:49,080
WELL, I'M GLAD
I GAVE YOU

1420
01:21:49,150 --> 01:21:51,350
AND YOUR SCHOOL
ONE LAST GO-AROUND,

1421
01:21:51,420 --> 01:21:53,950
BUT IN THE END
I GOT NOTHING BUT USED.

1422
01:21:54,020 --> 01:21:57,290
BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T
GET THE SCHOLARSHIP?

1423
01:22:01,860 --> 01:22:04,230
IS THAT ALL THERE IS?

1424
01:22:04,300 --> 01:22:06,050
GET OUT OF
YOUR FANTASY WORLD!

1425
01:22:06,120 --> 01:22:08,200
AFTER THE CRUSADERS
GET DESTROYED

1426
01:22:08,270 --> 01:22:10,030
ON THAT FIELD TONIGHT,

1427
01:22:10,120 --> 01:22:11,640
THIS TOWN
WILL DISAPPEAR.

1428
01:22:11,710 --> 01:22:13,470
AND GOD, SCHULER,

1429
01:22:13,540 --> 01:22:15,270
AND YOUR SILLY
LITTLE PAMPHLETS

1430
01:22:15,340 --> 01:22:16,380
AREN'T GONNA CHANGE THAT.

1431
01:22:25,640 --> 01:22:27,520
I TELL YOU WHAT.

1432
01:22:29,920 --> 01:22:31,790
SUPREME COURT OR NOT,
I'M PRAYING.

1433
01:22:31,860 --> 01:22:34,230
SO ANYONE WHO WANTS TO,
TAKE A KNEE.

1434
01:22:38,670 --> 01:22:41,300
Stadium crowd chanting:
CRUSADERS! CRUSADERS!

1435
01:22:41,370 --> 01:22:45,970
CRUSADERS! CRUSADERS!
CRUSADERS! CRUSADERS!

1436
01:22:54,880 --> 01:22:57,400
Announcer:
THE 2 TITANS OF ALABAMA

1437
01:22:57,470 --> 01:22:58,550
HIGH SCHOOL
FOOTBALL HISTORY:

1438
01:22:58,620 --> 01:23:01,120
THE ATHENS CRUSADERS
AND THE ROCK HILL RAIDERS,

1439
01:23:01,190 --> 01:23:02,220
ARE MOMENTS FROM KICK-OFF.

1440
01:23:02,290 --> 01:23:05,620
A PACKED ATHENS STADIUM
IS READY

1441
01:23:05,690 --> 01:23:06,690
FOR ONE OF THE MOST
ANTICIPATED

1442
01:23:06,760 --> 01:23:08,560
STATE CHAMPIONSHIP
GAMES EVER.

1443
01:23:08,630 --> 01:23:11,930
SNOOT NINO, WHOSE MIRACLE
45-YARD FIELD GOAL

1444
01:23:12,000 --> 01:23:13,460
GOT THE CRUSADERS
IN THIS GAME,

1445
01:23:13,550 --> 01:23:15,320
KICKS OFF FOR ATHENS.

1446
01:23:20,570 --> 01:23:23,440
[STADIUM CROWD CHEERING]

1447
01:23:36,820 --> 01:23:38,120
ALL RIGHT, GOD,

1448
01:23:38,190 --> 01:23:41,630
YOU GOT SOMETHING
TO SAY TO ME?

1449
01:23:47,070 --> 01:23:48,700
I DIDN'T THINK SO.

1450
01:24:34,620 --> 01:24:37,220
ALWAYS NICE
TO BE NEEDED.

1451
01:24:38,790 --> 01:24:40,250
HOW DID YOU KNOW
I WAS HERE?

1452
01:24:40,320 --> 01:24:41,590
I WAS TIPPED OFF
'BOUT THE TIME

1453
01:24:41,660 --> 01:24:42,890
THE THIRD PIE
SHOWED UP.

1454
01:24:42,960 --> 01:24:44,320
AND WHEN
THE MAYOR CAME,

1455
01:24:44,390 --> 01:24:46,090
I WENT LOOKING.

1456
01:24:48,190 --> 01:24:49,660
I DON'T KNOW
HOW THIS GOT HERE.

1457
01:24:49,730 --> 01:24:52,510
PEOPLE IN THIS TOWN
TAKE CARE OF THEIR OWN.

1458
01:24:52,580 --> 01:24:55,320
I TOOK A CUSTOMARY FEE

1459
01:24:55,390 --> 01:24:58,870
AS YOUR LANDLORD.
[CHUCKLES]

1460
01:25:02,290 --> 01:25:03,470
Announcer:
AS MOST EXPERTS PREDICTED,

1461
01:25:03,540 --> 01:25:04,980
THE CRUSADERS LOOK HOPELESS

1462
01:25:05,050 --> 01:25:07,250
AGAINST THE ROCK HILL
MACHINE.

1463
01:25:07,330 --> 01:25:08,380
8 YARDS FOR THE RAIDERS...

1464
01:25:08,450 --> 01:25:09,530
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1465
01:25:09,600 --> 01:25:10,650
TOUCHDOWN, ROCK HILL...

1466
01:25:10,720 --> 01:25:13,350
ROCK HILL 37, ATHENS 3
AT HALFTIME.

1467
01:25:13,420 --> 01:25:15,190
YES.

1468
01:25:15,260 --> 01:25:17,460
GOOD JOB, SON,
THAT WAS A BEAUTIFUL CATCH.

1469
01:25:17,520 --> 01:25:19,860
GOOD JOB.

1470
01:25:19,930 --> 01:25:21,330
SHERMAN...

1471
01:25:21,390 --> 01:25:23,090
YOU HIT LIKE
A TON OF BRICKS.

1472
01:25:23,160 --> 01:25:27,330
THAT QUARTERBACK
GONNA BE SORE FOR A MONTH.

1473
01:25:27,400 --> 01:25:29,370
SNOOT, GREAT KICK,
GREAT KICK.

1474
01:25:29,440 --> 01:25:31,800
YOU SENT IT INTO ORBIT.

1475
01:25:31,870 --> 01:25:33,100
GOOD JOB.

1476
01:25:36,380 --> 01:25:37,740
LISTEN UP, BOYS.

1477
01:25:41,080 --> 01:25:43,820
WE GONNA LOSE.

1478
01:25:43,880 --> 01:25:45,980
MAKE NO MISTAKE,
WE GONNA LOSE.

1479
01:25:48,720 --> 01:25:49,720
IT'S GONNA BE
THE WORST ROUT

1480
01:25:49,790 --> 01:25:52,090
IN THE HISTORY
OF ALABAMA PLAYOFF FOOTBALL.

1481
01:25:54,760 --> 01:25:56,800
BUT IT WAS WORTH IT.

1482
01:25:59,850 --> 01:26:05,240
YOU ARE FINALLY ONE UNIT.

1483
01:26:05,310 --> 01:26:08,310
FINALLY ONE BODY.

1484
01:26:11,580 --> 01:26:15,150
YOU RESURRECTED SOMETHING
THAT WAS LOST.

1485
01:26:18,020 --> 01:26:19,280
Elvis:
ARE YOU ON EMPTY, COACH?

1486
01:26:23,520 --> 01:26:25,010
IS THAT ALL YOU GOT?

1487
01:26:32,100 --> 01:26:34,470
YOU ALL STARTED
WITHOUT ME.

1488
01:26:38,610 --> 01:26:41,140
COACH?

1489
01:26:56,520 --> 01:27:01,130
LOOK, I THINK WE ALL KNOW
WHY I CAME TO ATHENS.

1490
01:27:01,190 --> 01:27:03,630
IT WASN'T FOR THE SCHOOL

1491
01:27:03,700 --> 01:27:06,260
OR EVEN THIS TEAM.

1492
01:27:06,330 --> 01:27:07,500
AND I NEVER THOUGHT

1493
01:27:07,570 --> 01:27:10,770
15 PLAYERS
COULD GET THIS FAR.

1494
01:27:12,270 --> 01:27:14,510
AND WE GET HERE
ONLY TO FIND OUT

1495
01:27:14,570 --> 01:27:18,340
THAT NONE OF US IS
GETTING THE SCHOLARSHIP,

1496
01:27:18,410 --> 01:27:21,980
THE SCHOOL'S
STILL GONNA CLOSE DOWN,

1497
01:27:22,050 --> 01:27:24,320
AND WE'VE GOT--

1498
01:27:24,380 --> 01:27:27,520
I MEAN, WE'RE PLAYING
A TEAM WE CAN'T BEAT.

1499
01:27:30,320 --> 01:27:32,190
DOESN'T SEEM WORTH IT.

1500
01:27:35,360 --> 01:27:38,130
BUT FOR SOME REASON,

1501
01:27:38,200 --> 01:27:40,430
THOSE STANDS ARE PACKED.

1502
01:27:42,640 --> 01:27:46,200
THE FANS ARE
STILL CHEERING, AND--

1503
01:27:46,270 --> 01:27:48,540
AND I'VE GOT ENOUGH
GET-WELL PIES

1504
01:27:48,610 --> 01:27:50,240
TO LAST ME A YEAR.

1505
01:27:53,180 --> 01:27:54,550
THEY'RE HERE
BECAUSE THEY BELIEVE

1506
01:27:54,610 --> 01:27:57,050
IN ATHENS TRADITION
AGAIN.

1507
01:28:00,990 --> 01:28:03,860
AND WE HAD SOMETHING
TO DO WITH THAT.

1508
01:28:07,090 --> 01:28:10,830
THAT'S SOMETHING
I'VE NEVER HAD BEFORE.

1509
01:28:16,340 --> 01:28:19,070
SO LET'S GIVE THIS TOWN

1510
01:28:19,140 --> 01:28:22,970
ONE LAST GREAT HALF
OF ATHENS FOOTBALL.

1511
01:28:23,040 --> 01:28:24,680
IN THE FUTURE,

1512
01:28:24,750 --> 01:28:26,240
WHEN THEY THINK
ABOUT FOOTBALL

1513
01:28:26,310 --> 01:28:27,950
IN ATHENS, ALABAMA,

1514
01:28:28,010 --> 01:28:31,350
LET'S MAKE 'EM THINK
OF THE NEXT 24 MINUTES.

1515
01:28:31,420 --> 01:28:33,750
WE STILL GOT
SOMETHING LEFT HERE.

1516
01:28:33,820 --> 01:28:36,090
HEY, ROCK HILL
HASN'T BEEN OUTSCORED

1517
01:28:36,160 --> 01:28:37,790
FOR A HALF IN 3 YEARS.

1518
01:28:37,860 --> 01:28:40,460
WE WIN THIS HALF,
WE GOT OUR PRIDE!

1519
01:28:40,530 --> 01:28:41,460
Player: COME ON!

1520
01:28:41,530 --> 01:28:43,630
THIS GAME STARTS
OVER RIGHT NOW!

1521
01:28:43,700 --> 01:28:44,700
Player:
YEAH! COME ON!

1522
01:28:44,760 --> 01:28:47,120
HEADS UP!
ACT LIKE JACKIE!

1523
01:28:47,180 --> 01:28:49,150
LISTEN UP, DOGS!

1524
01:28:49,220 --> 01:28:51,740
Y'ALL WANT TO PUT
ONE MORE DOWN IN THE BOOK?

1525
01:28:51,810 --> 01:28:53,420
YOU GONNA DO IT RIGHT.

1526
01:28:59,330 --> 01:29:01,760
SHERMAN NATERS.

1527
01:29:06,770 --> 01:29:08,300
I KNOW YOU'LL KEEP
THE PRIDE OF THIS JERSEY

1528
01:29:08,370 --> 01:29:10,210
ALIVE FOR ME, SON.

1529
01:29:10,270 --> 01:29:11,770
YES, SIR.

1530
01:29:20,130 --> 01:29:21,280
JACKSON.

1531
01:29:28,160 --> 01:29:29,590
WELCOME.

1532
01:29:37,100 --> 01:29:38,200
HEY.

1533
01:29:38,270 --> 01:29:40,270
THINK
I GOT YOUR NUMBER.

1534
01:29:40,340 --> 01:29:43,570
TRADITION'S REAL IMPORTANT
ROUND THESE PARTS.

1535
01:29:58,350 --> 01:29:59,690
ELVIS.

1536
01:30:02,130 --> 01:30:03,160
THIS ONE'S SEEN
A BIT OF WEAR,

1537
01:30:03,230 --> 01:30:07,350
BUT I THINK IT WANTS
ONE MORE GAME.

1538
01:30:07,430 --> 01:30:09,260
I JUST CAN'T--

1539
01:30:09,330 --> 01:30:11,700
TURN IT DOWN
IS WHAT YOU CAN'T.

1540
01:30:11,770 --> 01:30:13,230
MY BOY IS WATCHING.

1541
01:30:13,300 --> 01:30:15,800
NOW YOU GIVE IT
ALL YOU GOT, ELVIS.

1542
01:30:17,540 --> 01:30:19,640
GONNA GET BLOOD ON IT.

1543
01:30:19,690 --> 01:30:21,810
WELL, THAT'S
WHY IT'S CRIMSON.

1544
01:30:29,420 --> 01:30:31,150
DON'T GET FANCY.

1545
01:30:31,220 --> 01:30:32,820
HIT 'EM!

1546
01:30:32,890 --> 01:30:34,520
LET'S SHOW 'EM
SOME BARNYARD FOOTBALL!

1547
01:30:34,590 --> 01:30:35,760
1, 2, 3...

1548
01:30:35,830 --> 01:30:37,160
Team: CRUSADERS!

1549
01:30:37,230 --> 01:30:38,990
CRUSADERS!

1550
01:30:42,370 --> 01:30:46,200
[CROWD CHEERS]

1551
01:30:50,070 --> 01:30:52,540
Crowd chanting:
CRUSADERS! CRUSADERS!

1552
01:30:52,590 --> 01:30:55,080
CRUSADERS! CRUSADERS!

1553
01:30:55,150 --> 01:30:58,510
CRUSADERS! CRUSADERS!

1554
01:30:58,580 --> 01:31:00,110
PRAY FOR ME.

1555
01:31:00,180 --> 01:31:01,580
WHY ARE YOU
DOIN' THIS?

1556
01:31:01,650 --> 01:31:04,120
I'M A CRUSADER.

1557
01:31:08,730 --> 01:31:10,120
Announcer: DURING
OUR COMMERCIAL BREAK,

1558
01:31:10,190 --> 01:31:12,690
THE CRUSADERS
BURST ON TO THE FIELD

1559
01:31:12,760 --> 01:31:15,230
IN THE CRIMSON JERSEYS
THAT WERE RETIRED

1560
01:31:15,300 --> 01:31:16,330
12 YEARS AGO.

1561
01:31:16,400 --> 01:31:17,500
AND IN AN ODD TWIST,

1562
01:31:17,570 --> 01:31:19,600
THEY SET UP A CHALK BOARD
AT THE END OF THE FIELD.

1563
01:31:19,670 --> 01:31:22,740
I'M NOT SURE
WHAT THAT'S ALL ABOUT.

1564
01:31:22,810 --> 01:31:23,840
YOU CAN'T
CHANGE UNIFORMS

1565
01:31:23,910 --> 01:31:25,810
IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE GAME.

1566
01:31:25,880 --> 01:31:27,240
WELL, ACTUALLY THOSE
WEREN'T OUR UNIFORMS.

1567
01:31:27,310 --> 01:31:29,280
THESE ARE--
THESE ARE OUR UNIFORMS.

1568
01:31:29,350 --> 01:31:30,910
COME ON, JOHN.

1569
01:31:30,980 --> 01:31:32,480
IT'S THE LAST GAME
FOR THESE BOYS.

1570
01:31:34,350 --> 01:31:35,720
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1571
01:31:38,220 --> 01:31:40,420
HEY, THAT SUCKER'S
GOT MY JERSEY ON!

1572
01:31:40,490 --> 01:31:42,090
OH, LOOK AT THAT.

1573
01:31:42,160 --> 01:31:44,410
YOU CAN STILL SEE
THE BEER STAINS.

1574
01:31:44,480 --> 01:31:46,160
Announcer:
THAT'S ELVIS JACKSON

1575
01:31:46,230 --> 01:31:47,800
BACK TO RECEIVE THE KICKOFF.

1576
01:31:47,860 --> 01:31:49,400
APPARENTLY, HE IS
GONNA GIVE IT A GO

1577
01:31:49,470 --> 01:31:52,070
IN SPITE OF
A BADLY SPRAINED WRIST.

1578
01:31:52,140 --> 01:31:53,200
HE TAKES IT AT THE 5,

1579
01:31:53,270 --> 01:31:54,440
HESITATES
WAITING FOR A WEDGE.

1580
01:31:54,500 --> 01:31:55,790
UP TO THE 15,

1581
01:31:55,860 --> 01:31:58,540
HE FINDS A HOLE AT THE 20,
AND HE'S OFF TO THE RACES!

1582
01:31:58,610 --> 01:31:59,610
ONE MORE MAN TO BEAT!

1583
01:31:59,680 --> 01:32:02,660
HE'S GOT A BLOCKER,
AND HE'S GONE!

1584
01:32:02,730 --> 01:32:04,180
NOBODY'S GONNA CATCH HIM!

1585
01:32:04,250 --> 01:32:06,080
WEARING JACK SCHULER'S
NUMBER 7,

1586
01:32:06,150 --> 01:32:08,480
ELVIS JACKSON SCORES
THE FIRST TOUCHDOWN

1587
01:32:08,550 --> 01:32:09,520
OF THE SECOND HALF.

1588
01:32:09,590 --> 01:32:12,220
[CHEERING]

1589
01:32:16,660 --> 01:32:18,430
[REFEREE BLOWS WHISTLE]

1590
01:32:19,650 --> 01:32:22,000
THE TEAM'S BACK.

1591
01:32:25,070 --> 01:32:27,100
[SHOUTING AND CHEERING]

1592
01:32:50,890 --> 01:32:52,410
[WHISTLE BLOWING,
CHEERING]

1593
01:32:58,770 --> 01:32:59,830
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1594
01:32:59,900 --> 01:33:02,270
WELCOME TO ATHENS,
BABY! YEAH!

1595
01:33:02,340 --> 01:33:03,360
WHOO!

1596
01:33:08,450 --> 01:33:09,380
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1597
01:33:10,560 --> 01:33:12,410
NOW YOU CALL
A TIME-OUT?

1598
01:33:12,480 --> 01:33:13,450
WE'RE UP BY 20!

1599
01:33:13,520 --> 01:33:15,550
I AM NOT GONNA GIVE THEM
THE SATISFACTION!

1600
01:33:28,160 --> 01:33:29,400
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1601
01:33:29,470 --> 01:33:30,900
[CROWD CHEERS]

1602
01:33:47,280 --> 01:33:48,400
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1603
01:33:50,450 --> 01:33:52,650
Brian: SET! HUT!

1604
01:33:52,720 --> 01:33:53,720
HIKE!

1605
01:33:57,490 --> 01:33:58,690
HUT!

1606
01:33:58,760 --> 01:33:59,760
1, 2, HUT!

1607
01:34:15,300 --> 01:34:17,380
Brian: 10...HUT! HUT!

1608
01:34:21,250 --> 01:34:22,380
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1609
01:34:22,440 --> 01:34:24,020
OH, COME ON!
WHAT ARE YOU, BLIND?!

1610
01:34:24,090 --> 01:34:26,020
OH, GIVE US
A BREAK!

1611
01:34:27,890 --> 01:34:29,660
Announcer:
BRIAN SCHULER IS DOWN

1612
01:34:29,730 --> 01:34:33,430
AFTER TAKING A VICIOUS HIT
FROM CHRIS NORMAN.

1613
01:34:33,500 --> 01:34:34,560
HE'S GOTTA BE EXHAUSTED.

1614
01:34:34,630 --> 01:34:36,160
HE'S TAKEN A BEATING
THE WHOLE GAME.

1615
01:34:40,200 --> 01:34:41,300
WHERE YOU FEEL IT?

1616
01:34:41,370 --> 01:34:43,470
EVERYWHERE.

1617
01:34:43,540 --> 01:34:44,470
HELP ME UP.

1618
01:34:44,540 --> 01:34:46,910
NO, NO, NO, NO.
YOU PLAYED A GOOD GAME.

1619
01:34:46,960 --> 01:34:48,460
I'M PROUD OF YOU, BRIAN.

1620
01:34:49,610 --> 01:34:51,910
YASH, YOU SWITCH
TO QUARTERBACK.

1621
01:34:53,480 --> 01:34:54,750
COACH...

1622
01:34:55,950 --> 01:34:58,320
YOU'RE NOT TAKIN' ME
OUT OF MY LAST GAME.

1623
01:34:58,390 --> 01:35:00,040
I CAN'T THROW, BUT...

1624
01:35:01,720 --> 01:35:02,960
WE CAN RUN.

1625
01:35:07,360 --> 01:35:09,500
WHAT'S LOST COMMANDMENT
NUMBER ONE?

1626
01:35:09,570 --> 01:35:11,230
LET THE BONE ROLL.

1627
01:35:14,270 --> 01:35:16,200
LET THE BONE ROLL!

1628
01:35:16,270 --> 01:35:17,770
All: YEAH! COME ON!

1629
01:35:21,640 --> 01:35:23,480
Announcer: WITH THE CLOCK
WINDING DOWN,

1630
01:35:23,550 --> 01:35:26,450
ATHENS RETURNS
TO THE WISHBONE OFFENSE.

1631
01:35:26,500 --> 01:35:27,920
PERHAPS COACH SCHULER WANTS

1632
01:35:27,980 --> 01:35:31,670
TO GIVE THE CRUSADER FAITHFULS
ONE LAST LOOK AT IT.

1633
01:35:31,760 --> 01:35:33,620
THAT'S THE WAY
THE BONE ROLLS!

1634
01:35:35,960 --> 01:35:38,490
WE WILL NOT
LOSE THIS HALF

1635
01:35:38,560 --> 01:35:41,200
TO A TEAM
OF 15 PLAYERS!

1636
01:35:52,070 --> 01:35:53,210
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1637
01:35:57,810 --> 01:35:58,950
Announcer:
AND ATHENS CALLS TIME-OUT

1638
01:35:59,020 --> 01:36:00,710
WITH THE BALL
ON THE 30-YARD LINE.

1639
01:36:00,780 --> 01:36:03,550
THEY HAVE TIME
FOR ONE LAST PLAY.

1640
01:36:10,730 --> 01:36:12,290
ALL RIGHT, GENTLEMEN,

1641
01:36:12,360 --> 01:36:13,360
LET'S GET IT GOIN'.

1642
01:36:13,410 --> 01:36:17,870
YOU READY TO WEAR
SUPERMAN'S CAPE?

1643
01:36:17,930 --> 01:36:18,870
[LAUGHS]

1644
01:36:18,930 --> 01:36:20,030
ON ONE.

1645
01:36:20,100 --> 01:36:21,650
READY...
All: BREAK!

1646
01:36:21,720 --> 01:36:23,540
[CHEERING]

1647
01:36:30,680 --> 01:36:32,510
WE'RE GONNA SEND YOU
HOME TO MAMA, BOY.

1648
01:36:32,570 --> 01:36:35,180
[ROARS]

1649
01:37:14,060 --> 01:37:15,860
[CHEERING]

1650
01:37:46,190 --> 01:37:47,720
DON'T YOU GUYS GET IT?
YOU LOST.

1651
01:37:47,790 --> 01:37:49,690
[LAUGHS] YEAH.

1652
01:37:49,760 --> 01:37:52,280
Announcer: ROCK HILL
HAS DEFEATED THE CRUSADERS

1653
01:37:52,350 --> 01:37:53,990
62-32,

1654
01:37:54,060 --> 01:37:58,100
BUT NO ONE IN ATHENS
CARES ABOUT THAT RIGHT NOW.

1655
01:37:58,170 --> 01:37:59,400
AND, IF YOU DON'T MIND,

1656
01:37:59,470 --> 01:38:02,870
THIS BROADCASTER'S
GONNA SHUT UP AND APPLAUD.

1657
01:38:02,940 --> 01:38:05,440
[CHANTING]
CRUSADERS! CRUSADERS!

1658
01:38:05,510 --> 01:38:08,410
CRUSADERS! CRUSADERS!

1659
01:38:08,480 --> 01:38:10,710
CRUSADERS! CRUSADERS!

1660
01:38:12,150 --> 01:38:14,250
GOTTA BE THE FIRST TIME
THE LOSING TEAM'S

1661
01:38:14,320 --> 01:38:16,250
TORN DOWN THE GOALPOST.

1662
01:38:16,320 --> 01:38:17,420
[LAUGHING THROUGH TEARS]

1663
01:38:17,490 --> 01:38:18,750
YOU BETCHA.

1664
01:38:18,820 --> 01:38:20,420
COME ON, WHAT ARE
WE WAITIN' FOR, TEE?

1665
01:38:20,490 --> 01:38:21,770
LET'S GO
GET A RIP ON 'EM!

1666
01:38:21,840 --> 01:38:23,360
GREAT JOB, BRIAN.

1667
01:38:23,430 --> 01:38:24,460
THANKS, COACH.

1668
01:38:35,140 --> 01:38:36,100
WELL...

1669
01:38:36,170 --> 01:38:37,540
WELL,
IT'S ABOUT TIME.

1670
01:38:37,610 --> 01:38:38,970
[LAUGHS]

1671
01:39:04,070 --> 01:39:05,670
I'M GLAD
YOU CAME BACK.

1672
01:39:13,540 --> 01:39:15,310
KEEP THAT JERSEY,
SON.

1673
01:39:17,880 --> 01:39:19,910
YOU WERE BORN
TO WEAR THAT.

1674
01:39:26,790 --> 01:39:28,260
ELVIS JACKSON?

1675
01:39:32,400 --> 01:39:34,090
I'M SO PROUD
OF YOU. [LAUGHS]

1676
01:40:34,720 --> 01:40:35,920
Rachel: GOD...

1677
01:40:35,990 --> 01:40:38,860
I KNOW MIRACLES
HAPPEN EVERY DAY.

1678
01:40:38,930 --> 01:40:40,660
JUST SOMETIMES
IN DIFFERENT WAYS

1679
01:40:40,730 --> 01:40:42,930
THAN WE ASKED.

1680
01:40:43,000 --> 01:40:44,730
WE DIDN'T SAVE OUR SCHOOL,

1681
01:40:44,800 --> 01:40:46,730
BUT YOU BROUGHT
TRADITION AND PRIDE

1682
01:40:46,800 --> 01:40:47,800
BACK TO ATHENS.

1683
01:40:47,870 --> 01:40:50,640
SO, THANKS FOR SHOWIN' UP

1684
01:40:50,710 --> 01:40:54,580
AND SHOWIN' OFF
IN ATHENS, ALABAMA.

1685
01:40:54,640 --> 01:40:58,150
AND WHEN THEY TALK ABOUT
THE CRUSADERS' LAST HALF,

1686
01:40:58,210 --> 01:41:00,180
COACH SCHULER'S
FINAL STAND,

1687
01:41:00,250 --> 01:41:05,020
THE SPEED AND HEART
OF ELVIS JACKSON,

1688
01:41:05,090 --> 01:41:07,820
LET 'EM REMEMBER...

1689
01:41:07,890 --> 01:41:10,860
YOU ARE, WITHOUT A DOUBT.

